#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.47"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.47:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.47:0.2"
msgid "5. Uposathavagga "
msgstr "5. Sabbath "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 47. Dutiyavisākhāsutta → visākhāmanāpakāyikasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.47:0.3"
msgid "47. Dutiyavisākhāsutta "
msgstr "47. With Visākhā on the Loveable Gods "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.267, sc1
msgctxt "an8.47:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother. "

msgctxt "an8.47:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho visākhā migāramātā … pe … "
msgstr "Then Visākhā, Migāra’s mother, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "an8.47:1.3"
msgid "ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho visākhaṃ migāramātaraṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said to her: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an8.47:2.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhahi kho, visākhe, dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "“Visākhā, when they have eight qualities females—when their body breaks up, after death—are reborn in company with the Gods of the Lovable Host. "

msgctxt "an8.47:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi? "
msgstr "What eight? "

msgctxt "an8.47:2.3"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, mātugāmo yassa mātāpitaro bhattuno denti atthakāmā hitesino anukampakā anukampaṃ upādāya tassa hoti pubbuṭṭhāyinī pacchānipātinī kiṅkārapaṭissāvinī manāpacārinī piyavādinī … pe …. "
msgstr "Take the case of a female whose mother and father give her to a husband wanting what’s best for her, out of kindness and compassion. She would get up before him and go to bed after him, and be obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an8.47:3.1"
msgid "Cāgavatī kho pana hoti. "
msgstr "She’s generous. "

msgctxt "an8.47:3.2"
msgid "Vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgā payatapāṇinī vossaggaratā yācayogā dānasaṃvibhāgaratā. "
msgstr "She lives at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share. "

msgctxt "an8.47:3.3"
msgid "Imehi kho, visākhe, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatīti. "
msgstr "When they have these eight qualities females—when their body breaks up, after death—are reborn in company with the Gods of the Lovable Host. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an8.47:4.1"
msgid "Yo naṃ bharati sabbadā, "
msgstr "She’d never look down on her husband, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:4.2"
msgid "niccaṃ ātāpi ussuko; "
msgstr "who’s always keen to work hard, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ sabbakāmadaṃ posaṃ, "
msgstr "always looking after her, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:4.4"
msgid "bhattāraṃ nātimaññati. "
msgstr "and bringing whatever she wants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an8.47:5.1"
msgid "Na cāpi sotthi bhattāraṃ, "
msgstr "And a good woman never scolds her husband "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:5.2"
msgid "issāvādena rosaye; "
msgstr "with jealous words. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:5.3"
msgid "Bhattu ca garuno sabbe, "
msgstr "Being astute, she reveres "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:5.4"
msgid "paṭipūjeti paṇḍitā. "
msgstr "those respected by her husband. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an8.47:6.1"
msgid "Uṭṭhāhikā analasā, "
msgstr "She gets up early, works tirelessly, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:6.2"
msgid "saṅgahitaparijjanā; "
msgstr "and manages the domestic help. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:6.3"
msgid "Bhattu manāpaṃ carati, "
msgstr "She’s loveable to her husband, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:6.4"
msgid "sambhataṃ anurakkhati. "
msgstr "and preserves his wealth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an8.47:7.1"
msgid "Yā evaṃ vattati nārī, "
msgstr "A lady who fulfills these duties "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:7.2"
msgid "bhattu chandavasānugā; "
msgstr "according to her husband’s desire, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Manāpā nāma te → manāpakāyikā (si, mr)
msgctxt "an8.47:7.3"
msgid "Manāpā nāma te devā, "
msgstr "is reborn among the gods "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.47:7.4"
msgid "yattha sā upapajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "called ‘Loveable’.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.47:7.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

